### Signup - create account
POST {{host}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "P@ssw0rd!",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

### Signin - get access & refresh tokens
POST {{host}}/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "P@ssw0rd!"
}

### Refresh - exchange refresh token for new tokens
# If your refresh flow uses Authorization header with the refresh token:
POST {{host}}/auth/refresh
Authorization: Bearer {{refreshToken}}

### Logout - revoke server-side session / refresh token
POST {{host}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Get Profile - current user info
GET {{host}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Change Password
PATCH {{host}}/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "P@ssw0rd!",
  "newPassword": "N3wP@ssw0rd!"
}

### Status - auth check
GET {{host}}/auth/status
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

# Notes:
# 1) After signin, copy accessToken into @accessToken and refreshToken into @refreshToken for subsequent requests.
# 2) Adjust host if different. If refresh token is sent via cookie in your app, use the cookie mechanism instead of Authorization header.